, Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Mawde","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin):","habitational name from Mold in Flintshire, Wales, which name derives from Anglo-Norman French <i>mont haut</i> ‘high hill’ (Latinised as <i>mons altus</i>), the Norman name for Bailey Hill on which the castle stood. The name <i>de Montalt</i>, <i>de Mohaut</i> was borne by an Anglo-Norman aristocratic family who acted as castle wardens there but who had their chief seat in Riddlesden in Yorkshire, where the surname proliferated as <i>Mawhood</i> and <i>Maude</i>. In the 17th century one branch of the family acquired lands in Ireland. The Maude baronetcy of Dundrum, Tipperary, was created in 1705 for Robert Maude. His son Cornwallis Maude, Baron de Montalt, was created first Viscount Hawarden in 1793.   Mowatt   is the Scottish form of the name, from a different branch of the same family.","occasionally from Middle English and Norman French female personal name <i>Mahald</i> or <i>Maud</i>, which are Old French forms of ancient Germanic <i>Mahthild</i> (Latinised as <i>Matilda</i>), composed of the Germanic elements <i>maht</i> ‘might, power’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This personal name partly owed its great popularity among Normans in England to the fact that it was the name of the wife (<i>c.</i> 1031–83) of William the Conqueror. Surnames derived from this personal name are found in many forms and spellings, for example,   Mould   and   Moll  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mall","meanings":["English: from the medieval female personal name <i>Mall</i>, a common form of <i>Mald</i> or <i>Maud</i>. See also   Maude   and   Moll  . It had several pet forms; see   Malin  ,   Malkin  , and   Mallet  .","Indian (northern states): from Sanskrit <i>malla</i> ‘strongman, wrestler’."]},{"name":"Till","meanings":["English: from the Middle English female personal name <i>Till</i>, a pet form of Old French <i>Matild(e)</i> (in its Latin form <i>Matilda</i>), which was an alternative to <i>Maud</i>; see   Maude   2. A diminutive form occurs in   Tillotson  .","North German: variant of   Thiel  ."]},{"name":"Mault","meanings":["English: variant of   Maude   2."]},{"name":"Mowatt","meanings":["Scottish (northeastern): habitational name from Mold (Flintshire), see   Maude   1. The distinctive Scottish form of the name has arisen from a shift of stress in <i>Mohaut</i> from the second to the first syllable. In Caithness and Orkney, the surname is traditionally pronounced ‘Mode’."]},{"name":"Mould","meanings":["English:","from the Middle English female personal names <i>Mold</i>, <i>Moud</i>, or <i>Molt</i>, shortened forms of Anglo-Norman French <i>Mahold</i>, a common variant of <i>Mahald</i>; see   Maude   2.","habitational name from Mold (Flintshire, Wales)."]}]},{"name":"Jeffery","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Geoffrey  , common in the Middle Ages (as reflected in surnames such as <i>Jefferson</i>). This is now the usual spelling of the name both in North America and Britain. Well-known bearers include the novelist and former British politician  Jeffrey Archer  (  b. 1940 ), the British conductor  Jeffrey Tate  (  b. 1943 ), and the American soul singer  Jeffrey Osborne  (  b. 1951 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Jeffry","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Geoffrey  , common in the Middle Ages (as reflected in surnames such as <i>Jefferson</i>). This is now the usual spelling of the name both in North America and Britain. Well-known bearers include the novelist and former British politician  Jeffrey Archer  (  b. 1940 ), the British conductor  Jeffrey Tate  (  b. 1943 ), and the American soul singer  Jeffrey Osborne  (  b. 1951 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Jeffery Mawde was born in 1457, in Witnesham, Suffolk, England. He had at least 1 son with Margaret. He died in 1540, in his hometown, at the age of 83."},"et":{"1457–1540":"1457–1540","1454–Female":"1454–Surnud","1477–1532":"1477–1532","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","1532":"1532","1454":"1454","1540":"1540","Northowram, Yorkshire, England":"Northowram, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Witnesham, Suffolk, England":"Witnesham, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1457–1540":"1457–1540","1454–Female":"1454–Kuollut","1477–1532":"1477–1532","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","1532":"1532","1454":"1454","1540":"1540","Northowram, Yorkshire, England":"Northowram, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Witnesham, Suffolk, England":"Witnesham, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1457–1540":"1457–1540","1454–Female":"1454–Décédée","1477–1532":"1477–1532","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","1532":"1532","1454":"1454","1540":"1540","Northowram, Yorkshire, England":"Northowram, Everwyck, Angleterre","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Witnesham, Suffolk, England":"Witnesham, Suffolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Jeffery Mawde est né en 1457, à Witnesham, Suffolk, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Margaret. Il est décédé en 1540, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 83 ans."},"de":{"1457–1540":"1457–1540","1454–Female":"1454–Verstorben","1477–1532":"1477–1532","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","1532":"1532","1454":"1454","1540":"1540","Northowram, Yorkshire, England":"Northowram, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Witnesham, Suffolk, England":"Witnesham, Suffolk, England","lifeSummary":"Jeffery Mawde wurde 1457 in Witnesham, Suffolk, England geboren. Er hatte mit Margaret mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1540 im Alter von 83 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1457–1540":"1457–1540","1454–Female":"1454–Desede","1477–1532":"1477–1532","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","1532":"1532","1454":"1454","1540":"1540","Northowram, Yorkshire, England":"Northowram, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Witnesham, Suffolk, England":"W